body:
I'll add a reduced test case shortly, but the gist of this issue is large expressions can be spilled into a temporary wire in procedural regions, even when disallowLocalVariables is set. For example, in psuedo-ir:

```mlir
sv.always ... {
  sv.if <huge expression> {
  }
}
```

can become:

```mlir
sv.always ... {
  wire _tmp = <huge expression>;
  sv.if _tmp {
  }
}
```

I think we will need to enhance the large expression spilling logic to also respect `disallowLocalVariables`. Essentially, I believe we need something similar to this logic in PrepareForEmission: https://github.com/llvm/circt/blob/24a47bda3a264c6ec7b18c6f8bbac96295725d79/lib/Conversion/ExportVerilog/PrepareForEmission.cpp#L464-L466.

This issue is basically about addressing this comment: https://github.com/llvm/circt/blob/24a47bda3a264c6ec7b18c6f8bbac96295725d79/lib/Conversion/ExportVerilog/PrepareForEmission.cpp#L481-L484
